    body: "## What's Changed\n* Update documentation by @doctashay in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1767\n* maybe fix bridge blast by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1784\n* [decompiler] support for jak 2 by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1781\n* game/speedrunning: Add struct with relevant information to facilitate Auto Splitting by @xTVaser in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1775\n* game: fix transition from fullscreen (not borderless) to windowed by @xTVaser in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1786\n* decomp: add docstring support to relevant places in all-types by @xTVaser in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1753\n* Added screenshot hotkey by @sardap in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1776\n* release: inform the launcher repo when a release is cut by @xTVaser in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1788\n* jak1: put the auto-splitting marker in C++ so it can be quickly found by @xTVaser in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1791\n* fix tie lod and intro cutscene linux crash by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1794\n* fix opengl error when screenshotting with msaa off by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1795\n\n## New Contributors\n* @sardap made their first contribution in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1776\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/compare/v0.1.25...v0.1.26",
