    body: "## What's Changed\r\n* [decompiler] fix memory leak on empty pairs by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1635\r\n* separate language settings into 3 settings/options by @ManDude in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1636\r\n* Reduce overall draw count for multidraw by @Francessco121 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1639\r\n* [jak2] decomp gkernel, setup offline tests by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1638\r\n* fix typo by @Brent-Hickey in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1645\r\n* split game framebuffers to allow custom resolutions/shaders by @ManDude in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1641\r\n* improvements to custom level blender import by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1649\r\n* Fix exclusive fullscreen refresh rate by @Francessco121 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1643\r\n* Fix instanced sprite distort renderer not always using the most recent sine table by @Francessco121 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1646\r\n* [graphics] Another possible way to handle windowed by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1653\r\n* [gfx] add more annoying opengl texture initialization by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1654\r\n* [sparticle] workaround for 150fps crashes by @water111 in https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/pull/1655\r\n\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/open-goal/jak-project/compare/v0.1.18...v0.1.19",
